description: From French vendre, from Old French vendre, from Latin vendere, from vēnum (“(something for) sale”) + dare (“to give”).

entries.meaning: The act of vending or selling; a sale.
(UK, Australia, dated) The total sales of coal from a colliery.

verbs.description: vend (third-person singular simple present vends, present participle vending, simple past and past participle vended)

entries.meaning: Synonym of sell, now especially to sell through a vending machine.
(programming, transitive, uncommon) To provide or export functionality, especially from an API.
The letter Ꝩ/ꝩ, used in Old Norse, related to the rune wynn (ᚹ, whence also Latin-script Ƿ/ƿ) but with the bowl open at the top, like a y.
examples: [...] a gramm. term, implying the use of the old letter 'vend' in spelling v-rungu, v-rangr, v-reiðr, see introduction to letter R; ...
